source.name: SSA Eligibility Counts By Census
source.description: SSA Eligibility Counts By Census March 2013.  This file shows how many children and adults were on welfare and MediCal programs in Alameda County during the month of March 2013.  The following programs are included: CalWORKs; which provides monthly cash assistance to very low income families with children; Food Stamps which provides benefits on a plastic card that can be swiped at stores to pay for food only; General Assistance provides monthly cash assistance to very low-income adults without children.  General Assistance (GA) clients who are considered employable are limited to 3 months of aid, while those consideren unemployable have no time limit.  Medi-Cal provides no cost or very low-cost health insurance to low income individuals and families.
